-- BTG Pactual Is in Talks to Buy Eight Brazilian Drugstores, Valor Reports
-- Telma Marotto
-- 2010-07-06T11:24:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/btg-pactual-is-in-talks-to-buy-eight-brazilian-drugstores-valor-reports.html

          
          
             Banco BTG Pactual SA, headed by  Andre Esteves , is in talks to acquire eight stores from Brazilian
pharmacy chain Farmacia dos Pobres, Valor Economico reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  
 The purchase of the stores in the northeastern state of
Pernambuco is part of BTGâ€™s plan to create a national chain of
drugstores through small and medium-sized acquisitions, Valor
said.  
